div.p:
A publication prototype has been created using XSLT stylesheets and Javascript to produce interactive HTML pages. The current version allows one to
read the reconstructed text of each manuscript;
open each gloss in a pop-up with a click on the lemma (each pop-up can be moved where one likes);
show interactive and optional layers of information, like textual variance (by means of a form of critical apparatus), distinction between glossing hands (by means of color), and critical notes.
